acity: 1; transform: none;"><h2 data-find-omitted="" class="sr-only select-none">Claude responded: The dataset most people use for this exact assignment is the Superstore Dataset (Final) on Kaggle — it's the same data Tableau ships as a built-in sample, so t…</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div data-find-omitted="" class="contents"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-[var(--msg-pill-py,0.375rem)]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="relative h-5 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 overflow-hidden transition-[width,margin-right] duration-150 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.25,0.9,0.3,1)] w-0 -mr-2"><div class="pt-1"><div aria-hidden="true"><div class="!w-5 !text-brand-200 w-8 text-accent-brand inline-block select-none" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100" class="w-full fill-current"><path d="m19.6 66.5 19.7-11 .3-1-.3-.5h-1l-3.3-.2-11.2-.3L14 53l-9.5-.5-2.4-.5L0 49l.2-1.5 2-1.3 2.9.2 6.3.5 9.5.6 6.9.4L38 49.1h1.6l.2-.7-.5-.4-.4-.4L29 41l-10.6-7-5.6-4.1-3-2-1.5-2-.6-4.2 2.7-3 3.7.3.9.2 3.7 2.9 8 6.1L37 36l1.5 1.2.6-.4.1-.3-.7-1.1L33 25l-6-10.4-2.7-4.3-.7-2.6c-.3-1-.4-2-.4-3l3-4.2L28 0l4.2.6L33.8 2l2.6 6 4.1 9.3L47 29.9l2 3.8 1 3.4.3 1h.7v-.5l.5-7.2 1-8.7 1-11.2.3-3.2 1.6-3.8 3-2L61 2.6l2 2.9-.3 1.8-1.1 7.7L59 27.1l-1.5 8.2h.9l1-1.1 4.1-5.4 6.9-8.6 3-3.5L77 13l2.3-1.8h4.3l3.1 4.7-1.4 4.9-4.4 5.6-3.7 4.7-5.3 7.1-3.2 5.7.3.4h.7l12-2.6 6.4-1.1 7.6-1.3 3.5 1.6.4 1.6-1.4 3.4-8.2 2-9.6 2-14.3 3.3-.2.1.2.3 6.4.6 2.8.2h6.8l12.6 1 3.3 2 1.9 2.7-.3 2-5.1 2.6-6.8-1.6-16-3.8-5.4-1.3h-.8v.4l4.6 4.5 8.3 7.5L89 80.1l.5 2.4-1.3 2-1.4-.2-9.2-7-3.6-3-8-6.8h-.5v.7l1.8 2.7 9.8 14.7.5 4.5-.7 1.4-2.6 1-2.7-.6-5.8-8-6-9-4.7-8.2-.5.4-2.9 30.2-1.3 1.5-3 1.2-2.5-2-1.4-3 1.4-6.2 1.6-8 1.3-6.4 1.2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Identified dataset source and architected step-by-step dashboard building guide</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Identified dataset source and architected step-by-step dashboard building guide</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">The dataset most people use for this exact assignment is the <strong>Superstore Dataset (Final)</strong> on Kaggle — it's the same data Tableau ships as a built-in sample, so tutorials and troubleshooting help are everywhere for it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Link:</strong> <a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/vivek468/superstore-dataset-final">https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/vivek468/superstore-dataset-final</a></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">It has Order/Ship dates, Region, Segment, Category/Sub-Category, Sales, Quantity, Discount, and Profit — perfect for the kind of "business insight" storytelling this task wants.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">One shortcut: if you're using <strong>Tableau Desktop or Tableau Public</strong>, you don't even need to download anything — go to File → Open and look for "Sample - Superstore" in the saved data sources, it's bundled in by default. For Power BI you'll need to download the Kaggle CSV and import it via Get Data → Text/CSV.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's how I'd walk through the task, mapped to those six hints:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. Pick the data story first, then the charts.</strong> Before opening Tableau/Power BI, decide on 3-4 business questions you want to answer, e.g. "Which regions/categories drive the most profit vs. loss?", "Is there a sales trend over time?", "Which sub-categories have high sales but low profit (discount problem)?", "Who are our most valuable customer segments?" Everything else follows from this.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Chart-to-question mapping:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Sales/Profit trend over time → line chart (Order Date on columns, Sales &amp; Profit on rows, dual axis)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Sales/Profit by Region or State → filled map or bar chart sorted descending</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Category/Sub-Category profitability → bar chart, sorted, color-coded red/green for loss/profit (this is usually the "aha" chart — Furniture sub-categories like Tables and Bookcases often lose money)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Discount vs. Profit relationship → scatter plot (Discount on x, Profit on y) — great for showing discounting is hurting margins</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Customer segment performance → stacked or grouped bar chart by Segment</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Avoid clutter:</strong> stick to 2-3 colors max with one accent color reserved only for the thing you want to highlight (e.g., gray bars, one red bar for the worst performer). Turn off gridlines, remove unnecessary legends if there's only one series, and don't put more than 4-5 charts on one dashboard.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>4. Add context to each chart:</strong> use Tableau's annotation/reference line feature (right-click on chart → Annotate, or Analytics pane → Average Line) to mark things like "Avg profit margin: 12%" or call out a specific outlier directly on the chart instead of leaving the viewer to figure it out themselves.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>5. Highlight key takeaways &amp; business insight:</strong> for each chart, write one sentence of "so what" — not "Sales by region chart" but "West region drives 32% of profit despite only 25% of sales — most efficient region." This sentence becomes your dashboard title or a text box under the chart.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>6. Build the summary dashboard/storyboard:</strong> in Tableau, use the Dashboard tab to combine 3-4 sheets, add a title text box at the top stating the overall insight (e.g. "Discounting above 20% is wiping out profit in Furniture"), and use Tableau's Story feature (Story tab) to sequence 3-4 dashboard "scenes" that walk through the narrative for your final deliverable. In Power BI, the equivalent is building one polished report page with a clear title, KPI cards at the top, and 3-4 supporting visuals below.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>7. Export:</strong> File → Export as PDF (Tableau) or File → Export → PDF / "Export to PDF" (Power BI), or just take clean screenshots of each dashboard page.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Want me to help you work through the actual chart logic or talking points for a specific question (like the discount-vs-profit one), once you've pulled the data in?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_ms_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; widt