 transform: none;"><h2 data-find-omitted="" class="sr-only select-none">Claude responded: Here's the full walkthrough in Tableau, from opening the file to exporting your final report.</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div data-find-omitted="" class="contents"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-[var(--msg-pill-py,0.375rem)]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="relative h-5 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 overflow-hidden transition-[width,margin-right] duration-150 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.25,0.9,0.3,1)] w-0 -mr-2"><div class="pt-1"><div aria-hidden="true"><div class="!w-5 !text-brand-200 w-8 text-accent-brand inline-block select-none" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100" class="w-full fill-current"><path d="m19.6 66.5 19.7-11 .3-1-.3-.5h-1l-3.3-.2-11.2-.3L14 53l-9.5-.5-2.4-.5L0 49l.2-1.5 2-1.3 2.9.2 6.3.5 9.5.6 6.9.4L38 49.1h1.6l.2-.7-.5-.4-.4-.4L29 41l-10.6-7-5.6-4.1-3-2-1.5-2-.6-4.2 2.7-3 3.7.3.9.2 3.7 2.9 8 6.1L37 36l1.5 1.2.6-.4.1-.3-.7-1.1L33 25l-6-10.4-2.7-4.3-.7-2.6c-.3-1-.4-2-.4-3l3-4.2L28 0l4.2.6L33.8 2l2.6 6 4.1 9.3L47 29.9l2 3.8 1 3.4.3 1h.7v-.5l.5-7.2 1-8.7 1-11.2.3-3.2 1.6-3.8 3-2L61 2.6l2 2.9-.3 1.8-1.1 7.7L59 27.1l-1.5 8.2h.9l1-1.1 4.1-5.4 6.9-8.6 3-3.5L77 13l2.3-1.8h4.3l3.1 4.7-1.4 4.9-4.4 5.6-3.7 4.7-5.3 7.1-3.2 5.7.3.4h.7l12-2.6 6.4-1.1 7.6-1.3 3.5 1.6.4 1.6-1.4 3.4-8.2 2-9.6 2-14.3 3.3-.2.1.2.3 6.4.6 2.8.2h6.8l12.6 1 3.3 2 1.9 2.7-.3 2-5.1 2.6-6.8-1.6-16-3.8-5.4-1.3h-.8v.4l4.6 4.5 8.3 7.5L89 80.1l.5 2.4-1.3 2-1.4-.2-9.2-7-3.6-3-8-6.8h-.5v.7l1.8 2.7 9.8 14.7.5 4.5-.7 1.4-2.6 1-2.7-.6-5.8-8-6-9-4.7-8.2-.5.4-2.9 30.2-1.3 1.5-3 1.2-2.5-2-1.4-3 1.4-6.2 1.6-8 1.3-6.4 1.2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Architected comprehensive Tableau walkthrough spanning data connection through dashboard creation</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Architected comprehensive Tableau walkthrough spanning data connection through dashboard creation</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's the full walkthrough in Tableau, from opening the file to exporting your final report.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 1 — Get the data in</strong><br>
Download the CSV from the Kaggle link, then open Tableau and click "Connect to Data" → Text File (CSV) (or Microsoft Excel if you download the .xls version). Tableau will show you a preview grid — check that Order Date and Ship Date are recognized as dates (you'll see a small calendar icon above the column; if it's showing as a string, click the icon and change the type to Date) and that Sales, Profit, Quantity, Discount show the "#" numeric icon.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 2 — Go to a new sheet and build Chart 1: Sales &amp; Profit trend over time</strong><br>
Drag Order Date onto Columns — Tableau auto-aggregates it to years, click the "+" on the green pill to drill to Quarter or Month if you want more detail. Drag Sales onto Rows, then drag Profit onto Rows again, then right-click the Profit axis and choose "Dual Axis" so both lines share the same chart. Right-click the Profit axis again → Synchronize Axis if the scales look off. Rename the sheet "Sales &amp; Profit Trend."</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 3 — Chart 2: Profit by Sub-Category (the "where are we losing money" chart)</strong><br>
New sheet. Drag Sub-Category onto Rows, Profit onto Columns. Click the Sort icon in the toolbar to sort descending. Drag Profit onto Color as well — this auto-creates a red-to-blue diverging color scale so loss-making sub-categories pop out in red. Rename the sheet "Profitability by Sub-Category."</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 4 — Chart 3: Discount vs Profit (the "discounting is killing margin" chart)</strong><br>
New sheet. Drag Discount onto Columns, Profit onto Rows. Tableau will plot one mark — change the Marks card dropdown from "Automatic" to "Circle," then drag Sub-Category onto Detail so you get one dot per sub-category instead of one aggregated dot. Add a trend line: Analytics pane (left side, next to Data pane) → drag "Trend Line" onto the chart, choose Linear. This visually proves whether higher discounts correlate with lower profit. Rename the sheet "Discount Impact on Profit."</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 5 — Chart 4: Sales by Region/State (map)</strong><br>
New sheet. Double-click State in the Data pane — Tableau auto-generates a map. Drag Sales onto Color. Right-click anywhere on the map → Map Layers, and you can turn on state borders for clarity. Rename the sheet "Sales by State."</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 6 — Clean up clutter on each sheet</strong><br>
For each sheet: right-click in the chart background → Format, then turn off gridlines and reduce them to "None" or a very light gray. On the Color legend, pick a simple 2-color palette (Tableau's default Orange-Blue Diverging works well for profit/loss). Remove the legend entirely on charts where it's redundant (e.g., if every bar is labeled already, you don't need a separate legend).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 7 — Add context with annotations</strong><br>
On the Profitability by Sub-Category chart, right-click the worst-performing bar (likely Tables or Bookcases) → Annotate → Mark, and type a one-line insight like "Losing money on every order due to high shipping cost relative to price." On the trend chart, go to Analytics pane → drag "Average Line" onto the Profit axis so viewers see whether recent months are above or below average.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 8 — Build the Dashboard</strong><br>
Click the "New Dashboard" tab at the bottom. Set the size to something like 1200x800 (Fixed size, under the Size dropdown on the left). Drag all four sheets onto the canvas — Tableau will auto-tile them, but drag the edges to resize so each chart is clearly visible. Add a Text object at the top (drag "Text" from the Objects list) and type your headline insight, e.g., "Discounting above 20% erases profit — Furniture sub-category is the biggest risk." Optionally add a filter: click a chart, click the funnel icon that appears, and choose "Apply to Worksheets → All Using This Data Source" so one filter (like Region) controls every chart at once.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 9 — Build the Story (your "storyboard" deliverable)</strong><br>
Click the "New Story" tab. Drag your dashboard onto the first story point, give it a caption like "Overview: Where we make and lose money." Click "Duplicate" to make a second story point, then click on a different chart or apply a filter to change what's shown, and update the caption to walk through your narrative — Overview → Where we're losing money → Why (discounting) → Where it's worst (region/state) → Recommendation. Aim for 3-5 story points total.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 10 — Export your deliverable</strong><br>
Go to File → Export → PDF (or File → Print to PDF), pick "Active Sheet" if you only want the dashboard/story, or "Entire Workbook" for everything. That PDF is your visual report deliverable.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Once you've got the charts built, send me a screenshot of any that look off (wrong colors, confusing layout, etc.) and I can help you fix the specific formatting.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_o8_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: