Validated dual-axis chart and charted next steps forward</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">That's exactly right — you've got a working dual-axis chart with Sales (blue, left axis) and Profit (orange, right axis) trending by year. You can already see the story forming here: both are climbing 2014→2017, which is a solid opening insight for your storyboard.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Two small optional polish steps before moving on:<br>
Rename the sheet so it's easy to find later — double-click the "Sheet 1" tab at the very bottom of the window and type "Sales &amp; Profit Trend."<br>
If you want the two lines easier to compare at a glance, right-click the right-hand Profit axis (the "90K... 10K... 0K" numbers) and choose "Synchronize Axis" — this lines up the scales so you can see if profit is growing proportionally to sales or falling behind.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Once you've renamed it, let's move to <strong>Chart 2: Profit by Sub-Category</strong> — this is the one that usually reveals the most interesting insight (which products are actually losing money).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Right-click on the sheet tab at the bottom and choose "New Worksheet" (or click the small new-sheet icon next to your sheet tabs). Then:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Drag <strong>Sub-Category</strong> from the Data pane onto <strong>Rows</strong>.<br>
Drag <strong>Profit</strong> onto <strong>Columns</strong>.<br>
Click the sort icon in the toolbar (the bars-with-arrow icon, usually near the top) to sort descending by profit.<br>
Drag <strong>Profit</strong> onto <strong>Color</strong> as well — this will auto-color the bars red for losses and blue/green for profit.</p>
