Identified duplicate screenshot and redirected toward worksheet creation</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">This still looks like the same Profitability by Sub-Category chart (Chart 2) — looks like the new worksheet for the scatter plot hasn't been created yet, and the annotation box is also still overlapping the tooltip text from before.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Let's knock out both real quick:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Fix the annotation overlap:</strong> click directly on the white annotation box border (around "Tables lose money on nearly every order...") and drag it down and to the left into the empty space below the Tables bar, away from where your mouse hovers over the chart.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Create the new worksheet for Chart 3:</strong> look at the very bottom of the Tableau window — you'll see small tabs labeled "Data Source," "Sales &amp; Profit Trend," "Sheet 2" (or whatever you renamed it), and a small icon that looks like a sheet with a "+" on it right next to the tabs. Click that "+" icon (or right-click any tab → New Worksheet) to open a blank sheet.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Once you're on the new blank sheet:<br>
Drag <strong>Discount</strong> onto <strong>Columns</strong>.<br>
Drag <strong>Profit</strong> onto <strong>Rows</strong>.<br>
Change the Marks dropdown (currently "Automatic") to <strong>Circle</strong>.<br>
Drag <strong>Sub-Category</strong> onto <strong>Detail</strong>.<br>
Go to the <strong>Analytics</strong> tab (next to "Data" at top-left) and drag <strong>Trend Line</strong> onto the chart, choosing <strong>Linear</strong>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Send a fresh screenshot once you're on that new blank sheet with the scatter plot built.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_ue_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: ce