.4-2.6 1-2.7-.6-5.8-8-6-9-4.7-8.2-.5.4-2.9 30.2-1.3 1.5-3 1.2-2.5-2-1.4-3 1.4-6.2 1.6-8 1.3-6.4 1.2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Weighed skipping cosmetic issue to advance progress</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Weighed skipping cosmetic issue to advance progress</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">No worries, that's a fiddly UI interaction in Tableau — let's not get stuck on it. Two options:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Option A — skip it for now:</strong> the annotation already shows the key insight, it's just visually overlapping the tooltip you happened to be hovering over when you took the screenshot. If you move your mouse away from the chart entirely (off to the side) and look again, it likely looks fine — the "tooltip" text only appears while your cursor is hovering over that bar. Try moving your mouse off the chart and check.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Option B — if it's a genuine permanent overlap:</strong> right-click directly on the annotation text (not the chart bar behind it) → Format. A panel may not open for repositioning, so instead just delete it and start fresh: right-click the annotation → Remove, then right-click on the Tables bar again → Annotate → Mark, and this time when the text box appears, click once on its edge/border (a thin gray line) to select it as a whole object — you should see small square handles appear at the corners. Once you see those handles, click and drag from the edge (not the middle, which just clicks into the text for editing).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Either way, don't spend more time on this — it's cosmetic. Let's keep moving to Chart 3 since that's higher value for your deliverable.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Click the small "+" icon next to your sheet tabs at the bottom of the screen (it creates a new worksheet), then:<br>
Drag <strong>Discount</strong> onto <strong>Columns</strong><br>
Drag <strong>Profit</strong> onto <strong>Rows</strong><br>
Change the Marks dropdown to <strong>Circle</strong><br>
Drag <strong>Sub-Category</strong> onto <strong>Detail</strong><br>
Go to the <strong>Analytics</strong> tab → drag <strong>Trend Line</strong> onto the chart → choose <strong>Linear</strong></p>
