Diagnosed mapping visualization glitch and prescribed geographic role fixes</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Almost there — the map rendered, but the color isn't showing because of the "49 unknown" badge at the bottom right corner. That tells you Tableau didn't recognize all 49 US states as proper geographic locations, so it's not plotting them with color yet.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Easiest fix: click directly on that <strong>"49 unknown"</strong> badge in the bottom-right corner. It'll open a dialog showing each unmatched location with a dropdown — but first try the quick auto-fix: it usually offers a "Match" or auto-suggestion right there since "State" is an obvious US field, just confirm it should match to US States.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">If that doesn't immediately resolve it, an even more reliable fix: drag <strong>Country</strong> from the Data pane onto the <strong>Detail</strong> button in the Marks card. Tableau's geocoding sometimes needs that extra context (Country = United States) to correctly place State names on the map, since some state names can be ambiguous globally.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Once states match, the map should zoom into the US automatically and color in by Sales (light to dark blue gradient based on your legend).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Send a screenshot after trying either fix.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_116_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; user-select: none; font