re&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div data-find-omitted="" class="contents"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-[var(--msg-pill-py,0.375rem)]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="relative h-5 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 overflow-hidden transition-[width,margin-right] duration-150 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.25,0.9,0.3,1)] w-0 -mr-2"><div class="pt-1"><div aria-hidden="true"><div class="!w-5 !text-brand-200 w-8 text-accent-brand inline-block select-none" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100" class="w-full fill-current"><path d="m19.6 66.5 19.7-11 .3-1-.3-.5h-1l-3.3-.2-11.2-.3L14 53l-9.5-.5-2.4-.5L0 49l.2-1.5 2-1.3 2.9.2 6.3.5 9.5.6 6.9.4L38 49.1h1.6l.2-.7-.5-.4-.4-.4L29 41l-10.6-7-5.6-4.1-3-2-1.5-2-.6-4.2 2.7-3 3.7.3.9.2 3.7 2.9 8 6.1L37 36l1.5 1.2.6-.4.1-.3-.7-1.1L33 25l-6-10.4-2.7-4.3-.7-2.6c-.3-1-.4-2-.4-3l3-4.2L28 0l4.2.6L33.8 2l2.6 6 4.1 9.3L47 29.9l2 3.8 1 3.4.3 1h.7v-.5l.5-7.2 1-8.7 1-11.2.3-3.2 1.6-3.8 3-2L61 2.6l2 2.9-.3 1.8-1.1 7.7L59 27.1l-1.5 8.2h.9l1-1.1 4.1-5.4 6.9-8.6 3-3.5L77 13l2.3-1.8h4.3l3.1 4.7-1.4 4.9-4.4 5.6-3.7 4.7-5.3 7.1-3.2 5.7.3.4h.7l12-2.6 6.4-1.1 7.6-1.3 3.5 1.6.4 1.6-1.4 3.4-8.2 2-9.6 2-14.3 3.3-.2.1.2.3 6.4.6 2.8.2h6.8l12.6 1 3.3 2 1.9 2.7-.3 2-5.1 2.6-6.8-1.6-16-3.8-5.4-1.3h-.8v.4l4.6 4.5 8.3 7.5L89 80.1l.5 2.4-1.3 2-1.4-.2-9.2-7-3.6-3-8-6.8h-.5v.7l1.8 2.7 9.8 14.7.5 4.5-.7 1.4-2.6 1-2.7-.6-5.8-8-6-9-4.7-8.2-.5.4-2.9 30.2-1.3 1.5-3 1.2-2.5-2-1.4-3 1.4-6.2 1.6-8 1.3-6.4 1.2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Identified layout issues and charted corrective dashboard refinements</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Identified layout issues and charted corrective dashboard refinements</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">This is very close to done — the dashboard itself looks clean and readable. Two things left:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. The title landed in the wrong spot</strong> — it's currently sitting between "Sales &amp; Profit Trend" and "Profitability by Sub-Category" on the left side only, instead of spanning the top of the whole dashboard. Click directly on the title text ("Furniture Discounting Erodes Profit...") once to select it — you should see a gray border with a small drag handle at the top of that text box. Click and drag that whole box up to the very top strip of the dashboard, above all four charts, so it reads as a header for the entire thing rather than a caption for just the left column.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. The annotation is still overlapping the Tables bar</strong> in Profitability by Sub-Category — this one's been stubborn through dragging, so let's just remove it and replace it with a stable caption instead, like we discussed: right-click on the orange Tables bar → Annotate → Remove, then drag a small Text box underneath that chart's title and type the same insight as plain text. Floating annotations in Tableau are notoriously fiddly to reposition, while a Text object in a fixed dashboard cell won't move on its own.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Once both of those are fixed, you're functionally done with the dashboard. At that point you have two options for your final "Visual report" deliverable:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Option A (simpler):</strong> Export this single dashboard straight to PDF — File → Export → PDF — and that satisfies the "Visual report" + "Create summary slide/storyboard" requirement in one shot, since your title text box already acts as the summary headline.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Option B (more thorough, matches "storyboard" literally):</strong> Build a Tableau <strong>Story</strong> (Story tab at the top) with 3-4 points that sequence through: Overview → Where we're losing money → Why (discount) → Where sales concentrate, each with its own one-line caption — then export that.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Given how clean the single dashboard already looks, Option A is honestly enough for this assignment unless your rubric specifically asks for multiple sequential slides. Which would you rather do?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_170_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settin