2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Diagnosed missing dashboard charts and formulated streamlined solution</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Diagnosed missing dashboard charts and formulated streamlined solution</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">That checkbox at the bottom-left — "Show dashboard title" — is actually a separate, much easier built-in feature. Tableau can auto-generate a title bar from the dashboard's own name, so you don't need to wrestle with a floating text box at all.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's the cleaner path:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. Rename the dashboard itself.</strong> Right-click the "Dashboard 1" tab at the very bottom of the screen → Rename. Type your full headline there, e.g. "Furniture Discounting Erodes Profit: Where the Business is Winning and Losing." Tableau will now show this as a proper title bar automatically, since "Show dashboard title" is already checked.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Delete the floating text box you made manually</strong> — it's now redundant and likely the reason your charts disappeared from view. Click on the "Furniture Discounting Erodes Profit" text box to select it (you should see a border with handles), then press Delete on your keyboard.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Check if your four charts are still there underneath.</strong> They should still exist — they were probably just hidden behind the floating text box if it got stretched to cover the canvas. After deleting it, look at the canvas; if it's empty, drag your four sheets (Sales &amp; Pro..., Profitability..., Discount..., Sales by State) from the Sheets list back onto the canvas, same as before.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">This gets you a properly positioned, auto-formatted title with zero manual dragging involved. Send a screenshot once you've renamed the dashboard and removed the floating box.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_192_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-hei