 it, the title spans the top, and all four panels are clearly readable. This matches the target layout well: one headline insight, four scannable charts, no clutter.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">You've now covered every hint from the task: right chart for each question, minimal clutter, a clear takeaway on the sub-category chart, context via the caption and trend line, business-focused framing (the title itself is an insight, not just a chart name), and a coherent visual narrative across the four panels.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">From here, you have two paths to finish the deliverable:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Quick finish:</strong> File → Export → PDF (or Export → Image). This single dashboard already satisfies "Visual report" and effectively works as your summary slide too, since the title functions as your headline insight.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>More thorough finish:</strong> If your rubric explicitly wants a "storyboard" as multiple sequential slides, click the <strong>Story</strong> tab at the top, drag this dashboard in as your first story point captioned "Overview," then duplicate it 2-3 more times, applying a filter or highlighting a different chart each time, with captions like "Where we lose money" → "Why: discounting" → "Where sales concentrate." Then export the Story instead.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Given how solid the single dashboard already looks, I'd go with the quick finish unless you know your instructor is specifically grading for multiple story points. Which way do you want to go?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_1ae_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: