story points (you've already been doing this for me throughout this whole conversation, so you know exactly how), and send them to me. I'll compile them into a polished Word or PDF report with your title, captions, and insights already laid out professionally — you won't have to deal with Tableau Public accounts, uploads, or any export menus at all.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's literally all you'd need to do:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click through each of your 4 story points in Tableau (Overview, Furniture is the problem, Why, Where sales concentrate).</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Take a clean screenshot of each one (just the visualization, not the whole Tableau window with menus if you can avoid it — though I can crop them if needed).</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload all 4 images here.</li>
</ol>
