ence student — having it on GitHub is also good portfolio practice.</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div data-find-omitted="" class="contents"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-[var(--msg-pill-py,0.375rem)]"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="relative h-5 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 overflow-hidden transition-[width,margin-right] duration-150 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.25,0.9,0.3,1)] w-0 -mr-2"><div class="pt-1"><div aria-hidden="true"><div class="!w-5 !text-brand-200 w-8 text-accent-brand inline-block select-none" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100" class="w-full fill-current"><path d="m19.6 66.5 19.7-11 .3-1-.3-.5h-1l-3.3-.2-11.2-.3L14 53l-9.5-.5-2.4-.5L0 49l.2-1.5 2-1.3 2.9.2 6.3.5 9.5.6 6.9.4L38 49.1h1.6l.2-.7-.5-.4-.4-.4L29 41l-10.6-7-5.6-4.1-3-2-1.5-2-.6-4.2 2.7-3 3.7.3.9.2 3.7 2.9 8 6.1L37 36l1.5 1.2.6-.4.1-.3-.7-1.1L33 25l-6-10.4-2.7-4.3-.7-2.6c-.3-1-.4-2-.4-3l3-4.2L28 0l4.2.6L33.8 2l2.6 6 4.1 9.3L47 29.9l2 3.8 1 3.4.3 1h.7v-.5l.5-7.2 1-8.7 1-11.2.3-3.2 1.6-3.8 3-2L61 2.6l2 2.9-.3 1.8-1.1 7.7L59 27.1l-1.5 8.2h.9l1-1.1 4.1-5.4 6.9-8.6 3-3.5L77 13l2.3-1.8h4.3l3.1 4.7-1.4 4.9-4.4 5.6-3.7 4.7-5.3 7.1-3.2 5.7.3.4h.7l12-2.6 6.4-1.1 7.6-1.3 3.5 1.6.4 1.6-1.4 3.4-8.2 2-9.6 2-14.3 3.3-.2.1.2.3 6.4.6 2.8.2h6.8l12.6 1 3.3 2 1.9 2.7-.3 2-5.1 2.6-6.8-1.6-16-3.8-5.4-1.3h-.8v.4l4.6 4.5 8.3 7.5L89 80.1l.5 2.4-1.3 2-1.4-.2-9.2-7-3.6-3-8-6.8h-.5v.7l1.8 2.7 9.8 14.7.5 4.5-.7 1.4-2.6 1-2.7-.6-5.8-8-6-9-4.7-8.2-.5.4-2.9 30.2-1.3 1.5-3 1.2-2.5-2-1.4-3 1.4-6.2 1.6-8 1.3-6.4 1.2-7.9.7-2.6v-.2H49L43 72l-9 12.3-7.2 7.6-1.7.7-3-1.5.3-2.8L24 86l10-12.8 6-7.9 4-4.6-.1-.5h-.3L17.2 77.4l-4.7.6-2-2 .2-3 1-1 8-5.5Z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate font-base">Evaluated GitHub feasibility for uploading Tableau deliverables directly</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Evaluated GitHub feasibility for uploading Tableau deliverables directly</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Yes, actually that's a clean way to deliver this, especially since you're a data science student — having it on GitHub is also good portfolio practice. Here's the easiest path using GitHub's website (no command line needed):</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. Create a new repository.</strong> Go to github.com, sign in, click the <strong>+</strong> icon top-right → <strong>New repository</strong>. Name it something like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">superstore-data-visualization</code> and click <strong>Create repository</strong>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Take your 4 story-point screenshots</strong> (same as before — click through each Tableau story point and screenshot it).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Upload the files.</strong> On your new repo's page, click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong>. Drag in your 4 screenshots, and optionally your Tableau workbook file (.twb or .twbx) too, so anyone can see the underlying work.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>4. Add a README</strong> (this is what makes it look like a real report instead of just loose files). Still on that same upload screen, scroll down — there's a box to commit directly, but for a proper README you'll want a separate step: after uploading the images, click <strong>Add file → Create new file</strong>, name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">README.md</code>, and paste something like this, adjusting filenames to match what you actually uploaded:</p>
<div role="group" aria-label="markdown code" tabindex="0" class="relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100"><div class="sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right"><div class="absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10"><button class="inline-flex
