ur repo — looking at your file list on the left, you've only got two files: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">README.md</code> and one called <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">data visualization and storytellin...</code> (truncated name). The README example I gave you used placeholder filenames like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">overview.png</code>, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">subcategory.png</code>, etc. — you'd need to either rename your actual uploaded files to match those exact names, or update the README to reference whatever you actually named your files.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Right now it looks like only one file got uploaded (possibly your Tableau workbook, given the name), not the 4 screenshots. Let's fix this properly:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. Go back to your repo's main page</strong> — click "superstore-data-visualization" at the top, or click "Return to the repository overview" on that error screen.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Check what's actually there.</strong> Click on that "data visualization and storytellin..." file to see what it actually is — is it your .twb/.twbx Tableau file, or one of your screenshots?</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Upload your 4 screenshots properly.</strong> Click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong>, and drag in your 4 story-point screenshots. As you drag them in, GitHub will show you the exact filenames it's using (likely something like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Screenshot 2026-06-30 at....png</code> unless you rename them first on your computer).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>4. Tell me the exact filenames</strong> GitHub shows once uploaded (or rename them beforehand to something simple like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">overview.png</code>, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">subcategory.png</code>, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">discount.png</code>, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">map.png</code> before dragging them in — much cleaner).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>5. I'll then give you the exact README markdown</strong> matching your real filenames, and you can paste it in to replace what's there now.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Want to go that route, or tell me what's currently in that single uploaded file first?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_1f9_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: cen