lass="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div style=""><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Take the <strong>full screen</strong> — all four charts together — exactly like the screenshot you just sent me. That's perfect.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Each of your 4 story points shows the same full dashboard (all 4 charts) but with a different caption tab highlighted at the top. So you'll end up with 4 screenshots, each one looking similar to what you just sent, but with a different story point tab selected at the top of each.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">So the process is:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Overview: Where we're making and losing money"</strong> tab → full screenshot ✅ (already done — the one you just sent)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Furniture is the problem: Tables and Bookcases lose"</strong> tab → full screenshot</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>"Why: higher discounts erode profit"</strong> tab → full screenshot</li>
